# Dependency Management

- Reuse existing project utilities before adding packages.
- Prefer small, focused, actively maintained dependencies.
- Check package health: maintenance activity, security advisories, ecosystem fit, and license.
- Keep production dependencies conservative; document why a new dependency is needed.
- Run the relevant audit/check command before committing lockfile changes when practical.
- Do not add deprecated packages or packages with unresolved critical vulnerabilities.
